  "name": "Conjure Volley",
  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "source": {
      "book": "Materia"
    },
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You fire a piece of ammunition from a ranged weapon or throw a weapon into the air and choose a point within range. Hundreds of duplicates of the ammunition or weapon fall in a volley from above and then disappear. Each creature of your choice in a 40-foot-radius, 20-foot-high cylinder centered on that point must make a Dexterity saving throw. A creature takes [[/r 8d8]] damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. The damage type is the same as that of the ammunition or weapon, and if the ammunition or weapon used has additional effects, they apply to each creature in the area.</p><p><strong>At Higher Levels</strong>. When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 6th level or higher, the damage increases by [[/r 1d8]] for each slot level above 5th.</p>",
